.TH MKD 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mkd \- create a directory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mkd
.RI [ \-p ]
.IR directory ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mkd
creates each
.I directory
with mode 0755 (rwxr-xr-x).
With
.BR \-p ,
all intermediate parent directories are also created as needed
(no error if the directory already exists).
This is the JLC equivalent of
.BR mkdir (1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-p
Create parent directories as needed.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Wrong number of arguments.
.TP
.B 2
.BR mkdir (2)
failed.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Create a single directory:
.EX
mkd projects
.EE
.TP
Create nested directories:
.EX
mkd -p a/b/c/d
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mkdir (1),
.BR del (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
